    "An adversarial context can lead to all kinds of ethical issues (Martens 2022).",
    "Aïvodji et al. (2019) examine the use of post-hoc explanations to fairwash or rationalize decisions made by an unfair prediction model, while Slack et al. (2020) and Lakkaraju and Bastani (2020) investigate the discriminatory characteristics of explanations.",
    "Imagine a model using a prohibited feature such as e.g., gender or race, or a feature that is linked to one of these e.g., zip code, when other more neat explanations are available.",
    "The model user could choose to ignore the discriminatory explanations and use another one instead.",
    "When considering the ethical consequences of disagreement, consensus amongst explanations might be desired."
  ],
